definition.value: A glycosyloxyflavone that is myricetin 3-O-[beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-rhamnoside] in which the hydroxy group at position 6 of the beta-D-glucosyl group has been converted to the corresponding acetate.  Identified in PMID: 23549747 Fig. S21 peak 4.

A glycosyloxyflavone that is myricetin in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted to the corresponding O-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucoside. Identified in PMID 29667287 Fig. S17, peak 8.
A methyl propenyl ketone in which the double bond has (E)-configuration. It is a key odorant responsible for the chestnut-like aroma in green tea.
A monoglyceride in which the acyl groups contain a total of 22 carbons and 4 double bonds
An omega-hydroxy-long-chain fatty acid that is palmitoleic acid [(9Z)-16-hexadec-9-enoic acid) which is substituted by a hydroxy group at the terminal carbon.
A hydroperoxyoctadecatrienoic acid that is (9Z,11E,15Z)-octadecatrienoic acid which is substituted at position 13 by a hydroperoxy group.
An O-acyl carbohydrate that is beta-D-glucopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by a 4-hydroxybenzoyl group.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy-long-chain fatty acid that is the conjugate base of (9Z,12Z)-octadeca-9,12-dienoic acid which has been substituted at position 17 by a hydroxy group.
A monoglyceride in which the acyl groups contain a total of 22 carbons and 5 double bonds.
A steroid acid that is 3beta-hydroxy-4alpha-methyl-5alpha-cholesta-8,24-diene in which the hydrogen at the 4beta position has been replaced by a carboxy group.
